  "rag_context": "The Elevator System is a crucial flight control surface responsible for modulating the aircraft's pitch. It focuses on rapid actuation speed (<50ms), high precision deflection accuracy (±0.1°), and structural durability with high-grade composites (>1500 MPa tensile strength). The system is designed to withstand operational environmental conditions from -40°C to +85°C with corrosion-resistant coatings. It receives precise electrical commands and converts them into mechanical deflections to achieve desired pitch attitudes, directly impacting the aircraft's stability and maneuverability. The system ensures redundant fail-safe operations and accommodates diverse aerodynamic conditions.",
